==German==

===Noun===
'''Rheininundationskollektenkasse''' ''f'', plural ''-n''

# the [[Rhine]] [[inundation]]s fund.

===Notes===

Although there is no 'longest word' in German, this one famously uses an entire line of iambic pentameter in Heinrich von Kleist's ''Der zerbrochene Krug'' [http://www.kleist.org/texte/DerZerbrochneKrug_L.pdf].